The Machakos government has been urged to desilt Portland Dam to end the acute water shortage in Athi River town.&ldquo;We urge the government to address the problem as a matter of urgency, the situation is worsening by the day,&rdquo; resident Joyce Ndunge said. She said many residents have stopped going to work to fetch water from the few private boreholes available. Children have also stopped going to school as they help their parents look for water, Ndunge said. Clarice Onyango said, &ldquo;We cannot do anything without water, women and children are the most affected.&rdquo;